{"questionId":"9066672","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the mass of aluminium, in g, that could be extracted from an appropriate solution by a charge of 48 250 C. Use sections 2 and 6 of the data booklet.</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">moles of electrons «= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{48250{\\text{ C}}}}{{96500{\\text{ C mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>48250</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>96500</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;C mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 0.5000 «mol» &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">moles of aluminium «= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.5000{\\text{ mol}}}}{3}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.5000</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;mol</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 0.1667 «mol»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">mass of aluminium «= 26.98 g mol<sup>–1</sup> × 0.1667 mol» = 4.50 «g»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Award <strong>[3]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066672","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the mass of aluminium, in g, that could be extracted from an appropriate solution by a charge of 48 250 C. Use s